'''Elkhead State Park''' is a Colorado state park located in Moffat and Routt counties in northwest Colorado, near [[Craig, Colorado|Craig]]. The park surrounds and includes Elkhead Reservoir. It is sometimes referred to as '''Elkhead Reservoir State Park'''.<ref>Colorado Parks & Wildlife.[http://cpw.state.co.us/placestogo/parks/ElkheadReservoir Elkhead Reservoir].</ref>

The reservoir is stocked with smallmouth bass and trout, and northern pike are being transplanted from the [[Yampa River]] to the reservoir. <ref>Craig Chamber of Commerce. [http://www.craig-chamber.com/Elkhead-Reservoir.html Elkhead Reservoir].</ref> Activities at the park include camping, fishing, boating, wildlife viewing, and hiking.

==Geography==
The park straddles the Routt / Moffat county line. The reservoir dams Elkhead Creek, which drains the [[Elkhead Mountains]], to the north. 

